唯一的方式就是隔离，继续隔离，将隔离进行到底。
The only way to do this is to isolate, continue to isolate, and follow through with isolation.
口述 | 池　莉整理|何映宇今天只有一个强烈的呼吁——已经呼吁多天了，要采取切实隔离措施与行动到社区！人们为了买食品蔬菜还在超市拥挤，极容易造成再次感染传播。
AT & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45
今是武汉封城隔离第十三天了，明天就满了十四天最长潜伏期，但武汉疫情还在蔓延攀升。
Wuhan closed the city for 13 days, tomorrow will be the longest incubation period of 14 days, but Wuhan epidemic is still spreading.
为什么不能“配给制”送菜到社区？公交车和单位公车都闲置着，为什么不动用全社会力量进行彻底隔离？纵然有再多医疗支援，抵挡得了烈性传染病的不断再传播吗？！眼下新型冠状病毒爆炸式的传播方式，是教科书上都没有见过的。
Why can't "rationing" deliver food to the community? Why not use all the community's efforts to isolate the bus and bus completely? Even with more medical support, can we prevent the retransmission of the coronavirus, a new form of coronavirus that has never been seen in textbooks.
对待烈性传染病，唯一的方式就是隔离，继续隔离，将隔离进行到底。
The only way to deal with a strong infectious disease is to isolate it, keep it isolated, and see it through.
所有隔离家庭急需的粮食蔬菜，我建议有条件的社区，直接从蔬菜公司的田间地头或者仓库送到各个社区，然后以“人不见人”的方式扫码交易，老弱病残家庭的粮食和蔬菜，由社区工作人员送上楼；没有条件的社区居民，可以通过网络寻找到活跃在附近社区的骑手小哥，依然以“人不见人”的方式付费交易，请他们把粮食和蔬菜送到家门口。
For all the food and vegetables needed by isolated families, I recommend that those in a position to do so send food and vegetables directly from vegetable companies' fields or warehouses to communities and send them upstairs in a "no-man's-eye" manner. Community residents without the means to find their jockeys active in nearby communities still pay for food and vegetables at their doorsteps.
“霍乱发生的那一天没有一点预兆。
"The day of the cholera outbreak was without warning.
天气非常闷热，闪电在遥远的云层里跳动，有走暴迹象。
The weather was very sultry. Lightning was beating in the distant clouds, showing signs of violence.
走暴不是预兆，在我们这个城市，夏天的走暴是再正常不过的事情。
Violence is not a sign, in our city, the summer storm is the most normal thing.
”这是我写的《霍乱之乱》的开头。
This is the beginning of my book The Cholera Incident.
《霍乱之乱》写于1997年5月21日的汉口，发表于1997年第六期《大家》杂志，这是来自于我个人专业工作经历的小说。
The Cholera Chaos, written in Hankou on 21 May 1997, was published in 1997 in the sixth issue of Everybody's Magazine, a novel from my personal professional work experience.
我曾经做了三年的流行病防治医生，当我不得不离开卫生防疫部门的时候，我觉得我应该把自己的担忧写成一部小说：人类尽可以忽视流行病，但是流行病不会忽视人类。
I had been an epidemiologist for three years, and when I had to leave the Sanitary and Prevention Department, I felt I should turn my fears into a novel: Man can ignore epidemics, but epidemics do not ignore human beings.
我们欺骗自己是需要付出代价的。
We have to pay a price for deceiving ourselves.
今年，我亲身经历了这样的“代价”。
This year, I have experienced this "price."
2020年1月22日夜将近23点的时候，单位突然来电话，紧急通知：从明天起，武汉市民实施隔离。
On the night of 22 January 2020, just before 23 o'clock, suddenly came a phone call, emergency notice: from tomorrow, Wuhan city residents to implement isolation.
我立即将家中食品蔬菜分为十四天的等分，每天少吃一点，吃得尽量简单一点，争取不要因为买菜而必须外出。
I immediately divided the household food and vegetables into 14 equal points, eat less everyday, eat as simple as possible, do not have to go out because of the purchase of vegetables.
但让我痛心的是，我看到不少人因食品短缺，去超市买菜，超市里可怕的是人与人接触，会造成再次传播与扩散，直接影响你和家人以及他人的生命安全，很可能导致武汉隔离前功尽弃。
However, I am saddened to see many people go to supermarkets to buy food due to food shortage, and the terrible contact between people in supermarkets can cause re-spread and spread, directly affecting your life and that of your family and others.
所以我在自己的生活小区微信群里发出了《给物业与业主的6条建议》，建议大家管住双腿，共同努力。
So I issued "6 Recommendations to Property Owners and Properties" in the micro-letter group of my living quarters, suggesting that we control both legs and work together.
我学过公共卫生，参加过流行病封锁隔离防治。
I studied public health, participated in the epidemic blockade isolation control.
我知道流行病最基本、也是最根本的专业知识就是——早发现、早隔离才能最有效防止病毒传播！尽管今天科技发达，这还是迄今为止最有效的传统方式。
I know that the most basic and fundamental knowledge of the epidemic is that early detection and early isolation are the most effective ways to prevent the spread of the virus.
只有让病毒吃不到人，这种新型冠状病毒才可能慢慢被饿死！我现在是所在生活小区的一名热心义工。
The new coronavirus could starve to death only if the virus could not be eaten! I am now an ardent volunteer in my community.
最近的我比平时的写作生活更加忙碌。
Recently I have been busier than usual in my writing life.
我觉得在大难面前，人人都要有慈悲怜悯之心，在保护好自己的同时要竭尽所能帮助他人，做一些具体有用的、对防疫有利的事情。
I feel that in the face of disaster, everyone should have compassion, while protecting themselves while doing everything possible to help others, to do something specific and useful, good for epidemic prevention.
在这场天灾面前，我们每一位市民都要反思：我曾经做错了什么？我生活方式的对与错在哪里？我怎样与大自然相处的？我为什么非要吃野味？这次疫情公布是否有延误？应该如何纠正补过？只有有效的、深入的反思才能不让悲剧再次发生。
In the face of this natural disaster, each of us citizens must reflect: What have I done wrong? What is the right and wrong with my way of life? How do I get along with nature? Why do I have to eat venison? Is there any delay in the announcement of this outbreak? How should it be corrected? Only effective, in-depth reflection can prevent the tragedy from happening again.
发生于武汉的新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎疫情，至今仍未得到有效控制并已向全国扩散，这是相当严重的疫情了，已经到了非常危急的时刻，这绝不是危言耸听！但还是有人没有意识到这一点。
The outbreak of pneumonia caused by the new coronavirus infection in Wuhan has not yet been brought under effective control and spread to the whole country.
这个时候我们需要的不是宣泄情绪，讲大道理，也不需要高调的口号，需要的是我自己应该怎么做，才能够对防疫有利。
What we need at this time is not catharsis, to talk big, not to speak high-sounding slogans, but what I should do myself to be able to benefit from the epidemic.
这段时间，我也看到还有人以爱的名义、情的借口，大肆地泛滥爱与情。
During this time, I also saw people in the name of love, love excuse, rampant spread of love and affection.
爱与情，都是好东西，然而绝对不可以滥用。
Love and affection are good things, but they should never be abused.
这是一场战争，战争必须让廉价的爱与情走开！唯有将严格隔离坚持到底，人类才有可能赢得胜利！征集令“战疫”成败，匹夫有责。
This is a war, war must let cheap love and love go away! Only by adhering to the strict isolation, can mankind win the victory!
《新民周刊》现面向全国征集新冠肺炎采访对象和真实故事：如果你是参与抗击新冠肺炎疫情的医护人员或其家属，我们希望聆听你的“战役”故事，也希望传达你的诉求。
If you are a health care worker or family member involved in the fight against pneumonia, we hope to hear your "battle" story and convey your message.
如果你是确诊、疑似患者本人或家属，我们希望了解你和家人如何“抗疫”的过程，让外界了解你的真实经历。
If you are a confirmed, suspected patient or family member, we would like to know how you and your family have responded to the epidemic and let the outside world know about your true experience.
如果你是疫情严重地区的普通市民，我们希望展现你的乐观，并倾听你所需的帮助。
If you are an ordinary citizen of a highly affected area, we hope to show your optimism and listen to the help you need.
如果你是公共服务人员或各类捐助者，我们希望看到你的“最美逆行”，记录下你的无私。
If you are a public service provider or a variety of donors, we want to see your "most beautiful retrograde" and record your selflessness.
……抗击新冠肺炎疫情，我们诚征对疫情了解的社会各界人士，提供相关线索，说出你的故事，让我们用新闻留存这一切。
To fight the New Crown Pneumonia epidemic, we sincerely invite all sectors of the community to understand the epidemic, provide relevant clues, tell your story, let us use the news to retain all this.
